I have been here several times over the past few years, but the service seems to have drastically changed. The indiam man who received my order told me I cannot add any of the free toppings (as it says on the menu). I have never had this issue and could add the toppings how much I wanted before. If you are not giving the free toppings anymore then you should remove it from the menu.  I also asked for some water, for which I know they give a small plastic cup, but this man charged a full regular fountain drink. All in all, it isn’t much, but the burger place seems to be very focused on making money regardless of how bad they make a customer feel or by changing their own policies.  I think I won’t go there again untill they go back to before or at least have a reasonable service. Not only is the food good and affordable, but Boz's finally fills the void for a burger joint which has existed in Charles Village for as long as I can remember: Charles Village has subs, burritos, pizza, Indian, Asian, and FINALLY SOME GOOD RED MEAT! I met the owner (or one of them) today on my third visit to Boz's and he was an incredibly kind and attentive guy. Who would have thought it would be some folks from India to bring good-old-fashioned American cuisine to this part of Baltimore??? My compliments to the chef. P.S. I can't imagine a bacon milkshake is good. In fact, the idea of it makes me queezy, but if that's your thing you should give it a try at Boz's. For reference, Boz's is very similar to Five Guys.
